reviews_data.review_text: I love this place! They are the only actual dog friendly coffee shop I have found in Uptown and I love all their coffee drinks

2nd location I’ve ventured to. What a nice place!
Food is fresh, coffee is good.
Great coffeeshop, service and staff were very nice and polite. Welcoming aesthetic to the place, enjoyed my time there and would recommend to come again.

This place is a vibe, all the workers are nice & chill!

The morning buzz & the vegan energy balls are good

Cool place to chill and do some work!

This place is truly a little gem. I come here from time to time and I’ve always gotten excellent service and good quality drinks. The staff is so sweet and nice, always answering any questions I have or suggesting new things for me to try. The place is very nice and cozy too. Will continue to come back!

If your ideal coffee shop its a small and modern place and you care most about great coffee,  and warm hospitality—then Coffee Republic Is for you. This is a local hidden gem well worth visiting. It's a perfect stop for a quality espresso or a seasonal latte when you're near Uptown Charlotte. The batistas are very friendly and  profesional and the quailty of the drinks are on point.

If you're in the mood for a cozy, laid-back spot to enjoy a great cup of coffee, Coffee Republic is definitely worth checking out. Located in Trade Street in Charlotte NC, this small but welcoming café has a modern and relaxing vibe where you can enjoy coffee and also some quiet time to read or even have a meeting.

It’s clear they take their coffee seriously here.
The baristas were very  friendly, also the wait isn’t much after you place your order.

This is the perfect spot for coffee enthusiasts and casual visitors alike. I’ll definitely recommend this place and for sure be back for more of their amazing drinks and chill vibe.

I came in this morning and was very pleased with my service and order. They seemed to be pretty busy, especially with only having 3 baristas on staff, but still worked together well to get my order to me. Lou was a key component to the team and I could tell she is a hard worker. I’m not always in Charlotte, but I always try to stop here to get my fix!
A pretty good coffee place! I got the salty dog and the milk was foamed excellently and the baristas were friendly as well. Definitely gonna come back
Great service!

Was staying in Charlotte on biz and decided to check this place out this morning, as I was tired of hotel coffee.    The cold brew was a bit too bitter and acidic, and didn’t have any nutty or other flavor profile notes.  I had the avocado toast as well, and although the bread and avocado were good, there was way too much chili flakes on it, which overpowered the whole dish.  The staff was very nice, but unfortunately disorganized.  It wasn’t at all busy when I went in, maybe six people.  With three staff behind the counter, one should each have a job on the production line (I.e., cashier/cold brews; barista; food).    But they all did everything and so orders got missed, and it took way too long - and then forgot my cold brew.  The atmosphere is pleasant and clean.  But if this is going to become a franchise chain, they need to step up their service and coffee game.
The coffee is great and we love the food but the app never works so online orders never go through. There also need to be more baristas on the clock because the wait times are way too long.

Really nice cafe for coffee and a breakfast sandwich! I recommend the pesto egg and cheese sandwich. It hit the spot. Tried the iced snickerdoodle. Just sweet enough without being overly sweet. They also had a menu of different flatbreads. Anyways glad we found this place both food and coffee is great! Would definitely come back and try something else!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee and friendly service! They also have good food and desserts.

From the moment we stepped inside, the friendly staff welcomed us with warm smiles and genuine enthusiasm. They took their time walking us through the menu, answering our questions with patience and charm. We ordered a nutty truffle coffee and a caramel frappe—both were simply divine. The truffle coffee was delightfully smooth, with rich cocoa notes and a satisfying depth, while the caramel frappe struck the perfect balance of creamy sweetness and caffeine kick. We left feeling thoroughly impressed and already excited for our next visit!

I don’t always love the drinks I get which is why I give it a 4. And that’s not at all due to the quality of how they’re made. The service here is really amazing. The staff has been consistent. As someone who’s lived in the gateway part of uptown for 3 years this was a third space this area really needed.

Very cute place. There is inside dining space and a little patio. I’ve tried their specially made drinks and they were good! It is a little pricey but it’s a coffee shop in uptown so that should be expected. I will definitely come back!

review_questions.Parking options: Free street parking, Paid street parking

reviews_data.review_text: Cool place to sit and hangout. Really nice and chill staff.
The spinach and cheese danish is sooooo good.

I passed by this place last week on my way to work, and this week I finally decided to give it a try. It’s a fantastic spot for morning coffee and breakfast. Unlike the typical “cozy” cafes with often awkward seating and odd decor choices, this one offers plenty of standard, comfortable tables and chairs - ideal for staying focused and getting things done if you try to sync up with work. It has a bright, inviting morning vibe. A large central counter adds a lot of character to the space, and it's practical, too. The equipment looks high-end, and the food and coffee are genuinely excellent. Everything is pleasantly clean, and the service is warm and welcoming. Highly recommended!

Great little place to grab a quick breakfast. We had the Aztec Mocha and Sugar Daddy signature lattes and a regular cappuccino and they were pretty good. The Aztec Mocha had a bit of spice to it which worked with the chocolate. We also had the quiches and the chorizo, egg and cheese on an English muffin which were decent.
Call to see if they’re open before you go.  Hours on google don’t match the actual hours they’re open.

Nice new coffee place with a nice look to it.  Service was excellent but the actual coffee in my latte was blah and kind of bitter.  I suspect it was arabica.

The health department rating in the window said 95 which is pretty terrible for a brand new place.

Will keep trying their different coffees and food offerings and hope I find some winners.

Came here the other day to grab some matcha after a long night. This spot caught my friends eye, so we finally decided to check it out.

First impression—it’s super clean, aesthetically pleasing, and has a good amount of space whether you want to sit inside or chill outside. It’s a cute place to catch up with work on a laptop or catch up with friends.

We were greeted right away, and the vibe was really welcoming. I ordered a tea and the strawberry matcha that’s been trending lately. I had to tweak it a bit—oat milk instead of regular and no cold foam since I’m lactose intolerant. The cashier was super patient, especially since I was ordering tea for a friend and we were a little all over the place with flavors. Shoutout to both the cashier and barista! They were both really kind and helpful.

Now, the matcha was just okay for me. Not bad, but not something I’d rush back for. That said, my friends really liked their drinks, so I think I just didn’t pick the right thing.

I’d come back to try one of their coffee options and hopefully sit around. The space is inviting and I saw outlets, which is always a plus.
Excellent and polite staff and a fun clean/environment. Huge selection of great breakfast and lunch food. Very convenient location, and dog friendly, free pup cups!
Good coffee and service, lots of drink options

reviews_data.author_title: Keep It A Secret Entertainment, LLC
reviews_data.review_text: Great time, good coffee, with excellent giveaways for the grand opening today!
Nice baristas, nice facility, but my goodness that coffee is not very good. :(

Great people great atmosphere.  I live in the northeast and found these by word of mouth and all I can say is wow!  They are super inviting and the staff is second to non.  I highly recommend the coffee republic brand and have been to almost all  the locations
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much, Michael! We're thrilled to hear that you enjoyed the welcoming atmosphere and our amazing team at Coffee Republic. It’s fantastic that word of mouth led you to us all the way from the Northeast—what a compliment! We truly appreciate your support and your kind words about our brand. 

Next time you're in Trade Street, we’d love to see you again at our coffee shop for another Iced Latte (or maybe something new to try!). See you soon! Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place! Great vibe and awesome coffee and drink selection. Really close to uptown too so easy to get to.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you, Laura! We're so glad you love the vibe and our coffee selection. Being close to uptown makes it even easier to stop by for your favorite drink! 

Next time you're in the area, why not visit Coffee Republic on Trade Street for another great coffee experience? See you again soon! Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee! Great atmosphere!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your kind words, Louise! We're delighted to hear you enjoyed the coffee and atmosphere. If you're ever in Trade Street, visit Coffee Republic for another fantastic coffee experience! We look forward to welcoming you again soon. Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text:
Ordered an iced vanilla latte and it was probably the worst iced coffee I have had in Charlotte. I’m not sure if the espresso sat too long or how they even make drinks (it looks like some sort of machine that mixes the syrup with the milk, almost like a gas station?) but I will not go back. I threw out the coffee and went to Starbucks. I tried to support something new but yeah, it’s a no go for me. Coco, Starbucks, Water Bean, etc… all nearby and so much better.

On the plus side, the energy ball is good.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Anthony,

We’re sorry to hear that your iced vanilla latte didn’t meet your expectations. We strive to serve quality coffee, and your feedback is valuable in helping us improve. Our drinks are crafted with fresh espresso, and we’ll certainly review our process to ensure consistency.

We’re glad you enjoyed the energy ball! If you’re ever open to giving us another try, we’d love to make it right. Feel free to reach out to us at daniel@coffeerepub.com so we can learn more about your experience.

Next time you’re in the Trade Street area, we invite you to visit Coffee Republic. We hope to see you again!


Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic
